<T>__{cut to:}
<L>__{exterior fifth ave. side of central park day}
<B>__{on ted and billy}
<A>__{tracking in front of them as they walk along the central park side of fifth ave. from their attitude it is clear that each of them, for their own reasons, is very nervous. ted's pov tracking forward about half a block away joanna paces back and forth. she hasn't seen them and it is clear that she is as nervous as they are.}
<B>__{another angle on ted and billy}
<A>__{ted stops, turns to billy and gives him a last minute check. then, spotting a smudge he takes his handkerchief, spits on it and wipes the child's chin. now satisfied, he takes billy's hand and they continue. suddenly:}
<B>__{closeup billy}
<A>__{as he spots his mother.}
<C>__{billy}
<D>__{mommy!}
<A>__{quick cut: joanna as she turns, spots billy, starts to run.}
<B>__{on billy}
<A>__{tracking with him as he lets go of ted's hand and starts to run flat out toward his mother. she kneels, opens her arms wide for him and he goes barreling into her, almost knocking her down from the impact.}
<C>__{joanna}
<P>__{(somewhere between laughter and tears)}
<D>__{oh, billy... oh my billy... oh my son...}
<B>__{wider shot}
<A>__{joanna gets to her feet and takes billy's hand.}
